me different options.

00:00:54.020 --> 00:00:58.060
And those were things that more
were about exercising the mind,

00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:00.060
trying to fight
epilepsy, which is

00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:01.900
a joining of both
sides of the brain

00:01:01.900 --> 00:01:04.730
together, firing seizures.

00:01:04.730 --> 00:01:08.080
So in the beginning
of that journey,

00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:12.970
I did a lot of mental drawings,
little different doctors

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:17.800
of putting puzzles together,
trying to use a focus.

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:21.220
And what it came
down to was actually

00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:25.420
a food diet and snowboarding,
which I owe a lot

00:01:25.420 --> 00:01:29.260
to my healing of epilepsy.

00:01:29.260 --> 00:01:34.120
This took about three years
of a certain kind of diet.

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:37.060
And snowboarding, I
kind of use that word

00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:41.350
as a healing tool for me because
it was a big focus for me.

00:01:41.350 --> 00:01:44.650
It's something I felt like
I was grounded in the world.

00:01:44.650 --> 00:01:47.092
And this is in the mid '80s.

00:01:47.092 --> 00:01:49.300
And I don't know if you know
a lot about snowboarding

00:01:49.300 --> 00:01:53.360
in the '80s and into the '90s,
it was not a welcome sport.

00:01:53.360 --> 00:01:55.780
And so that was
kind of, in a way,

00:01:55.780 --> 00:02:00.020
a perfect fit because I didn't
fit in any way in school.

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:02.800
And so my journey
with all of this--

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:04.570
again, kind of what
I owe to my parents

00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:08.330
is the OK of being different.

00:02:08.330 --> 00:02:10.509
And those things
is the things I've

00:02:10.509 --> 00:02:14.980
learned 20 years later on
why my career in snowboarding

00:02:14.980 --> 00:02:20.840
went the way it did and why I
did the things that I do now,

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:25.000
which is a lot about
just feeling in action,

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.550
doing things, seeing
where it goes,

00:02:27.550 --> 00:02:32.110
what resonates inside
to self growth.

00:02:32.110 --> 00:02:35.140
And in snowboarding, it
kind of put me in a spot

00:02:35.140 --> 00:02:37.780
where I kind of followed for
a while the World Tour, World

00:02:37.780 --> 00:02:39.695
Cup, did the competition.

00:02:39.695 --> 00:02:42.460
We were all developing
the sport together,

00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:45.520
so we kind of shaped
how things were run.

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:49.210
