years later I realized

00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:52.330
I was kind of growing out
of the competition scene.

00:02:52.330 --> 00:02:54.970
And with my childhood
of just trying

00:02:54.970 --> 00:02:58.390
to take on different
things different ways,

00:02:58.390 --> 00:03:00.640
I saw a different
perspective in snowboarding

00:03:00.640 --> 00:03:02.980
that wasn't developed yet.

00:03:02.980 --> 00:03:05.720
I was photographed a
lot in snowboarding.

00:03:05.720 --> 00:03:09.130
I had a lot of ideas at the same
time how to be photographed.

00:03:09.130 --> 00:03:12.010
Working with two different
minds to create an image

00:03:12.010 --> 00:03:13.910
can be very
challenging sometimes,

00:03:13.910 --> 00:03:18.160
especially when you're the
one on risk with your life

00:03:18.160 --> 00:03:23.030
and feeling the power of passion
for what you're actually doing.

00:03:23.030 --> 00:03:27.700
And so I've slowly started to
develop these different parts

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:29.500
of cameras, joining.

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:33.220
I hired someone to do some
soldering for some wires

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:36.260
and I've started
taking self portraits.

00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:38.140
This is in the late '90s.

00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:43.660
And I realized this was a huge
room, a space to figure out

00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:46.660
what else could come to.

00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:50.260
And at the time my career, I
was getting at an age where

00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:53.500
