And I realized that's
a lot to do with motion

00:24:29.740 --> 00:24:31.510
and back onto the golden ratio.

00:24:31.510 --> 00:24:33.880
I don't know if a lot about
the golden ratio, but it's

00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:37.279
the basics of quantum
physics, how we all built--

00:24:37.279 --> 00:24:39.070
everything else is kind
of built under that

00:24:39.070 --> 00:24:45.490
unless you go outside of that
equation, which we all do.

00:24:45.490 --> 00:24:47.920
But what I truly--
back to the heart

00:24:47.920 --> 00:24:52.210
has a natural instinct that
is based on the golden ratio,

00:24:52.210 --> 00:24:55.577
that I feel like is a great
balance to find out the stuff

00:24:55.577 --> 00:24:57.160
I'm struggling with,
as I was sharing.

00:24:57.160 --> 00:24:59.680
Like sometimes there's too much.

00:24:59.680 --> 00:25:01.480
Sometimes there's too little.

00:25:01.480 --> 00:25:05.260
And those are kind
of, I think, has a lot

00:25:05.260 --> 00:25:09.680
to do with being too much in the
past, too much in the future,

00:25:09.680 --> 00:25:11.450
or too much in the present.

00:25:11.450 --> 00:25:14.740
And so what I've learned,
back into the golden ratio,

00:25:14.740 --> 00:25:16.840
is to find things in thirds.

00:25:16.840 --> 00:25:19.960
You have the past,
present, and the future.

00:25:19.960 --> 00:25:21.760
The future we don't know.

00:25:21.760 --> 00:25:24.010
We have a way of
shaping that together.

00:25:24.010 --> 00:25:28.210
The past has already happened,
so we know what has been.

00:25:28.210 --> 00:25:32.560
And the present is of
right now, the simpleness

00:25:32.560 --> 00:25:38.470
of doing something that will
no longer be this moment.

00:25:38.470 --> 00:25:43.500
We can record it, pass it
on, which becomes the past.

00:25:43.500 --> 00:25:47.550
And so that is a way that I've
learned to stay in balance,

00:25:47.550 --> 00:25:54.830
to stay in health, and to
continue to trust the instinct.

00:25:54.830 --> 00:25:59.550
Because as I get older,
